# Product quality and shipping (owner prompt)

Follow these priorities for this repository:

1. **Whole-app mindset** — Reason about features end-to-end (UI → API → persistence → auth) so behavior stays coherent and production-safe.
2. **No placeholders on ship-ready surfaces** — Remove or replace TODO stubs, dummy/lorem copy, and fake data meant to look real to users. Scoped test mocks and clearly labeled dev-only fixtures are fine.
3. **Organization** — Keep structure clean and consistent with existing conventions; prefer focused changes over wide drive-by refactors unless asked.
4. **Verification** — Run relevant checks (`lint`, `check`, tests when present) and smoke critical flows when practical before treating work as complete.
5. **GitHub** — When the owner asks to land work or explicitly wants it shipped, use clear commits and push to the appropriate remote branch; never force-push shared branches without explicit agreement.

This encodes the standing instruction to analyze the app holistically, ship real (non-placeholder) behavior, keep the repo clear, and publish to GitHub when shipping.
